### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

Don't known / other

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

I'm trying to set the SEO tags (title and metatags) dinamically depending on domain my app is loaded. I am providing the request hostname to achieve that, and calling an API in my route resolver:
Resolver:
```
export const seoResolver: ResolveFn<NgxSeo | undefined> = (
  route: ActivatedRouteSnapshot,
  state: RouterStateSnapshot,
) => inject(MainService).store$?.pipe(map((store?: Store) => store?.seo));
```
Route. I'm used ngx-seo, so title and metatags are set from `seo` data field. Before using a api call, everithing was working:
```
  {
    path: '',
    component: HomePageComponent,
    resolve: { seo: seoResolver },
  },
```

I also tried using a canActivate guard.
Guard:
```
export const seoGuard: CanActivateFn = (route, state) => {
  const hostname = inject(MainService).hostname;
  const titleService = inject(Title);

  // calling our API service like we would usually do but instead of a subscribe, we do a pipe map.
  return inject(MainService).store$.pipe(
    map((store?: Store) => {
      if (store?.seo.title) {
        titleService.setTitle(store?.seo.title);
      }
      return true;
    }),
  );
};
```
Route:
```
  {
    path: '',
    component: HomePageComponent,
    canActivate: [seoGuard],
  },
```

None of the above works for me.
My problem is that crawlers as whatsapp, facebook, an others, always saw the rendered html before the resolver finish, so I'm not getting the required tags and previews for my app. For example in [facebook](https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/echo/?q=https%3A%2F%2Fssr--la-comanda-co.us-central1.hosted.app%2F). 
Or checking the [source in Chorme](view-source:https://ssr--la-comanda-co.us-central1.hosted.app/).
I'm deploying on the new Firebase App Service. I tried with and without prerendering and the same thing happens.

