### Description

`transform` function in the `@Input` decorator was introduced as a replacement of the `@Input() set`, but it doesn't allow to change the data type.
Before we did
```
interface UserData { name: string; surname: string; title: string; };

...

@Input() set user (data: UserData) {

    this.fullName = `${title} ${name} ${surname}`;

}

fullName: string;
```

So the data is shaped from one type to another one. While doing it in transform function causes strict templates errors.

### Proposed solution

```
interface UserData { name: string; surname: string; title: string; };

...

function toFullName (data: UserData): string {

  return `${title} ${name} ${surname}`;

}

...

@Input({ transform: toFullName }) user: UserData: 
```

